Author: jl777c#5810
Content: @ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢ the way the dice is provably random is that neither side knows both entropy values when they are betting

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the dealer generates the entropy tx (no idea why the chainmakers dont make more entropy tx with 0.0001 values)

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but it is only visible as the hash(entropy) the hentropy

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the bettor then picks a random dealer hentropy utxo adds his entropy in the clear

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: now the dealer can tell if it is a win or loss, if he is honest he pays out the wins immediately

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: if he doesnt and it times out, it must be a loss of dealer, ie automatic win, otherwise the dealer can just never payout wins
